SIMPLE: fervid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fervid
<hw>Fer"vid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fervidus</ets>, fr. <ets>fervere</ets>. See
<er>Fervent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very hot; burning;
boiling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mounted sun⟦br⟧
Shot down direct his <qex>fervid</qex> rays.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ardent; vehement; zealous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>fervid</qex> wishes, holy fires.</q>
<rj><qau>Parnell.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fer"vid*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fer"vid*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fervor</ent>⟦br⟧
